The paper deals with image denoising using graph-based methods, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of negative weights in the graph Laplacian construction is related to information theory (cs.IT) and linear algebra (cs.NA). The paper also discusses the improvement in filter quality, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and signal processing (cs.SI).
